===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|welth|lang=enm}}, {{term|welthe|lang=enm}}, {{term|weolthe||happiness, prosperity|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|*welþ}}, {{m|ang|*weleþu}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*waliþō||wealth}}.
Alternatively, possibly an alteration (due to similar words in {{term|-th|lang=enm}}: compare {{term|helth||health|lang=enm}}, {{term|derth||dearth|lang=enm}}) of {{term|wele||wealth, well-being, weal|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|wela||wealth, prosperity|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*walô||well-being, prosperity}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*wel-||good, best}}, equivalent to {{suffix|weal|th|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|weelde||wealth|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|weelde||wealth|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|welida|lang=goh}}, {{term|welitha||wealth|lang=goh}}. Related also to {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Wohl||welfare, well-being, weal|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|vel||weal, welfare|lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|väl||well-being, weal|lang=sv}}. More at {{l|en|weal}}, {{l|en|well}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} Weal; welfare; prosperity; good; well-being; happiness; joy.
# Riches; valuable material possessions.
# A [[great]] [[amount]]; an [[abundance]] or [[plenty]].
#: ''She brings a '''wealth''' of knowledge to the project.''
# [[power|Power]], of the kind associated with a great deal of money.

